30.08	Kilim	Kilim	Kilims are flat tapestry-woven carpets or rugs produced from the Balkans to Pakistan. Kilims can be purely decorative or can function as prayer rugs. Recently-made kilims are popular floor-coverings in Western households.	http://upload.wikimedia.org/wikipedia/en/thumb/8/84/Hotamis_Kilim_.jpg/220px-Hotamis_Kilim_.jpg
